  "original_title": "\u0ba4\u0bae\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bcd \u0b87\u0b9f\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 3 \u0baa\u0bc6\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0ba8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0bb0\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Suggest 3 names for Dammika's place",
      "author": "T. Saranya",
      "body_lines": [
        "The names of three members of the Podujana Peramuna have been nominated to fill the vacancy following the resignation of Member of Parliament Dammika Perora.",
        "However, Dhammika Perera has not yet officially announced that she will renounce her parliamentary membership.",
        "While there are unconfirmed reports that Member of Parliament Tammika Perera is resigning, the names of Sri Lanka Podujana Peremana Executive Secretary Renuka Perera, Southern Province Governor Wili Kamake and Central Environment Authority Chairman Siripala Amarasinghe have been nominated at the party level for the vacant position of Member of Parliament.",
        "Following former Finance Minister Bashil Rajapaksa's resignation as Member of Parliament on 09th of last month, Dammika Perera took oath as Member of Parliament on 22nd of last month through the national list.",
        "However, following the political changes that have taken place in the last few days, there have been reports that Member of Parliament Tammika Perera has decided to resign, although she has not yet officially announced her resignation to the Podujana Peramuna."
      ],
